Mandla Mandela and his wife, Rabia, are expecting their first child, the couple announced on Monday. &#8220;We are excited beyond words today to be celebrating, not only our first wedding anniversary, but also the fact that we are expecting our first bundle of joy in transit,&#8221; Mandla and Rabia said in a statement. &#8220;Mvezo Komkhulu will once again experience the pitter-patter of a young Mandela&#8217;s feet. It&#8217;s been an amazing year. We are truly blessed and very grateful for all the well wishes received.&#8221; Mandela is the grandson of former president Nelson Mandela. He wed his wife in February 2016 in a traditional Muslim Nikah ceremony. This is Mandela s fourth marriage. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.